Looks good.

Patch Set 6:

I was revisiting this change and started to think if this actually is smart way to log these errors. glance.common.exception.Forbidden contains _("You are not authorized to complete this action."). Now if we do not log some meaningful error message we will just get this line into the DEBUG logs.

I'd rather see meaningful log messages what was actually blocked by policy.

Ideas, anyone?

Patch Set 6:

Also that message itself does not define that it was actually blocked by policy.

Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

jokke: I agree. That message is at least misleading, since 'you' probably does not refer to the person reading the logs. I think just logging a specific message for policy violations, like

    "User was forbidden from completing action based on policy rules."

would be sufficient.

Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

Thanks for confirming that to me Louis.

I think this patch need more work before we should merge it.

Patch Set 8:

There was quite a lot of discussion about the logging levels when I was doing the refactoring for K&J logging. One thing we got to agreement with is that we most definitely should not log permission denied etc. messages on too high level to prevent users killing the logs with such events.

IMO the debug would be the least wrong thing to do here. What is the reasoning you changed those to warnings?

Patch Set 8:

With https://review.openstack.org/#/c/132552/ merged, I'm wondering if we're logging these exceptions at the right level. It's probably best to continue with what we're doing here and clean up the levels and the way we do logging (Ben's concern) in a separate changeset though.

Patch Set 8:

Erno they weren't changed to warnings, they were added as warnings by agileclipse originally. I've just been moving this through to get it into kilo. I'm going to change these to debug messages when I get around to fixing this up.
